In [22]:
def add_data_point(folder, image_file, measurement):
    fname = image_file.split("/")[-1]
    fname = folder + "/IMG/" + fname
    image = cv2.imread(fname)
    image = image[...,::-1]
    return image, measurement


def get_train_data(folder):
    lines = []
    with open(folder + "/driving_log.csv") as csvfile:
        reader = csv.reader(csvfile)
        for i, line in enumerate(reader):
            if i == 0:
                continue
            lines.append(line)
    tasks = []
    for line in lines:
        steering = float(line[3])
        # left
        tasks.append(delayed(add_data_point)(folder, line[1], steering + 0.2))
        # center
        tasks.append(delayed(add_data_point)(folder, line[0], steering))
        # right
        tasks.append(delayed(add_data_point)(folder, line[2], steering - 0.2))
    data = Parallel(n_jobs=50)(tasks)
    return data

images = []
measurements = []

# "data" folder is provided by udacity
# "train_data" folder is data I collected as below: 
# 1. data provided by Udacity
# 2. two laps of center lane driving
# 3. one lap of driving smoothly and counter-clockwisely
for folder in ["../data", "../center_lane_data", "../smooth_data"]:
    for image, measurement in get_train_data(folder):
        images.append(image)
        measurements.append(measurement)

# augment data by flipping image and measurement

augmented_images = []
augmented_measurements = []
for image, measurement in zip(images, measurements):
    augmented_images.append(image)
    augmented_images.append(cv2.flip(image, 1))
    augmented_measurements.append(measurement)
    augmented_measurements.append(measurement * -1)
In [24]:
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
%matplotlib inline

def plot_image(imgfile, label, flip=False, crop=False):
    imgfile = imgfile.split("/")[-1]
    imgfile = "../smooth_data/IMG/" + imgfile
    image = cv2.imread(imgfile)
    image = image[...,::-1]
    if flip:
        image = cv2.flip(image, 1)
    if crop:
        image = image[75:160-20,:,:]
    plt.imshow(image)
    plt.title(label)
    plt.show()


with open("../smooth_data/driving_log.csv") as csvfile:
    reader = csv.reader(csvfile)
    for i, line in enumerate(reader):
        if i == 0:
            continue
        else:
            plot_image(line[0], "center")
            plot_image(line[1], "left")
            plot_image(line[2], "right")
            plot_image(line[0], "center flip", flip=True)
            plot_image(line[1], "left flip", flip=True)
            plot_image(line[2], "right flip", flip=True)
            plot_image(line[0], "center crop", crop=True)
            plot_image(line[1], "left crop", crop=True)
            plot_image(line[2], "right crop", crop=True)
            break

In [26]:
# model architecture

model = Sequential()
model.add(Lambda(lambda x: x / 255 - 0.5, input_shape=(160, 320, 3)))
model.add(Cropping2D(cropping=((70, 25), (0, 0))))
model.add(Conv2D(24, (5, 5), strides=(2, 2), activation="relu"))
model.add(Conv2D(36, (5, 5), strides=(2, 2), activation="relu"))
model.add(Conv2D(48, (5, 5), strides=(2, 2), activation="relu"))
model.add(Conv2D(64, (3, 3), activation="relu"))
model.add(Conv2D(64, (3, 3), activation="relu"))
model.add(Flatten())
model.add(Dense(100))
model.add(Dropout(0.5))
model.add(Dense(50))
model.add(Dropout(0.5))
model.add(Dense(10))
model.add(Dense(1))

model.compile(loss='mse', optimizer='adam')
model.fit(X_train, y_train, validation_split=0.3, shuffle=True, nb_epoch=2)

model.save('model.h5')
